Welcome to Inbox by Gmail

What would you like to bundle?

Unbundled messages appear individually in the inbox. You can always change this later in settings.

Picture of Inbox user interface showcasing Bundles feature. Top item is a Promos Bundle. It has the Promos logo on the left, and the name of the bundle, Promos, next to it. The title of the bundle is the list of senders within the bundle (Blitz Air, Running Club, Rabbit facts). The next item is an abstract representation of an emall. The third item is the Purchases bundle. It has the Purchases logo on the left, and the name of the bundle, Purchases, next to it. The title of the bundle is the list of senders within the bundle (Shoehop, Creek Farms, Dollar Auctions, Two Wheel Deals). Picture of Inbox user interface showcasing Highlights feature. The top item is an email from Brighter Lights. Subject of the email is "Thank you for your order #239412". The email has a Highlight that has important information shown in a chip. On the left, the chip has an image of the ordered item as well as a badge announcing that the order is Shipped. On the right, the chip has the ordered item name (Vintage String Lights), the expected delivery date (October 17th), and a Track Package link. The rest of the items in the Inbox are abstract representations of email with no content. Picture of Inbox user interface showcasing Reminder feature. Top item is Reminder, with Reminder logo. Title of the reminder is buy tickets. Picture of Inbox user interface showcasing Snooze feature. Top item is Email from Andrea Jones. Subject of email is See you next week. Snippet is visible and starts with "Let's meet at". Pin, Snooze, Done and Dropdown buttons are visible. Snooze button is selected, and modal dialogue is shown with Snooze options available. The options are Tomorrow, Next Week, Someday, Pick a date and time and Pick a place.
